Story: Sebf6b0-1 — フォルダ pin の解決 (バックエンド)
Date: 2026-07-08
Branch: autopilot/smart-folder/Sebf6b0

## Changes

### packages/shared/src/schemas.ts
- Replaced `import { isValidVaultPath }` with `import { normalizeVaultFilePath, VaultPathError }`.
- Added `isValidPinPath()` helper: validates pin.path as either a note path (.md) or a folder path
  (no .md) using `normalizeVaultFilePath` — rejects traversal/hidden/absolute; does NOT append .md.
- Updated `smartViewPinItemSchema` to use `isValidPinPath` instead of `isValidVaultPath`, allowing
  folder paths (e.g. "projects", "projects/sub") in addition to note paths (e.g. "note.md").
- Backward compatible: existing .md note-pin paths remain valid.

### packages/server/src/routes/smart-folders.ts
- PUT handler: replaced `normalizeVaultPath` (which appended .md) with `normalizeVaultFilePath`
  (which preserves folder paths without .md). This ensures folder paths like "projects" are stored
  as-is, not incorrectly turned into "projects.md".
- GET /api/smart-folders/{id}/notes (pin branch): extended resolution logic:
  1. If noteMetaMap has an exact match for item.path → single NoteMeta (backward compatible note-pin).
  2. Else treat item.path as a folder: collect all notes where
     `n.folder === folderPath || n.folder.startsWith(folderPath + '/')`.
     Sort by path ascending for a stable result.
  3. Neither match → empty array (never errors).

